PN,35407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1778186660
OL,3,CPolling stations open as Scots elect
OL,4,Cnew Holyrood Parliament
OL,6,FThe party has been polling well for
OL,7,Fthe first time at Holyrood and looks
OL,8,Fpoised to win at least a dozen seats,
OL,9,Fwith one of the key battles being
OL,10,Fbetween Lord Malcolm Offord's party
OL,11,Fand Labour for second place.
OL,13,FAnas Sarwar has insisted the polls `
OL,14,Fsome of which put Labour in third
OL,15,Fplace ` are getting it wrong and his
OL,16,Fparty will defy the pollsters and
OL,17,Fpundits on Thursday, but it is a far
OL,18,Fcry from the success Labour
OL,19,Fexperienced at the 2024 election in
OL,20,FScotland.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/12
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1778186660
OL,3,CPolling stations open as Scots elect
OL,4,Cnew Holyrood Parliament
OL,6,FThe Scottish Labour leader cut ties
OL,7,Fwith Prime Minister Sir Keir Starmer
OL,8,Fin February, calling for him to stand
OL,9,Fdown in the wake of the Mandelson
OL,10,Fscandal, severing an alliance which
OL,11,Fhad held since the two took over their
OL,12,Frespective parties north and south of
OL,13,Fthe border.
OL,15,FThe Scottish Greens and the Lib Dems
OL,16,Falso look set for gains, according to
OL,17,Fthe polls, with the Greens forecast to
OL,18,Fbe in the running to win their first-
OL,19,Fever local constituency.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/12
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,355,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F354A1778186660
OL,3,CPolling stations open as Scots elect
OL,4,Cnew Holyrood Parliament
OL,6,FGreen co-leader Gillian Mackay said
OL,7,Fthat every vote for her party was a
OL,8,F"vote for a fairer, greener and
OL,9,Findependent Scotland and to reject the
OL,10,Fhatred and division of Reform UK".
OL,12,FShe insisted: "We don't have to accept
OL,13,Fa broken status quo. It's time to
OL,14,Fdemand better."
OL,26,@pD@AOUrD@aO]tD@OOUvD@OO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G9/12
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
